#### 3.2.5 Backend Relay System & Core Loop

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Receive user message & fetch session] --> B{Is there a pending question?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Parse & validate the answer]
    C --> D{Valid answer?}
    D -->|No| E[Return error + repeat question]
    D -->|Yes| F[Store answer in data dict]
    F --> G{More questions in current stage?}
    B -->|No| G
    G -->|Yes| H[Return next question]
    G -->|No| I[Move to next stage]
    I --> J{More stages?}
    J -->|Yes| G
    J -->|No| K[Generate final report]
    K --> L[Relay POST JSON to specific Spring Boot User Backend]
    K --> M[Return medical advice + tips]
```

At the finish line (`state_index == len(STAGES)`), `handle_message()` does two vital background operations:
1. Emits the object into an isolated log under `patient_records/`.
2. Connects dynamically to Python's `os.getenv("BACKEND_URL")` with fallback routes, appending a `patientInput` JSON string into an established Java Spring Boot controller via `/api/chatbot/complete?patientId={PATIENT_ID}`.

